keyFacts: The document is a government travel itinerary for Alexander Bittner Rossmiller, a Department of Justice employee, dated February 14, 2020.
The travel, occurring February 19-20, 2020, was from New York to Pensacola, Florida, and back, booked through the official CWT SatoTravel system.
The itinerary includes instructions that all modifications must be mailed to Steffany Rnefta-Smith at the Executive Office for United States Attorneys (EOUSA).
The total cost of the travel was $717.76, charged to a government payment card ending in 9931.
The purpose of the trip to Pensacola is not stated in the document.
